What "Extensions" Means
This refers to Phase 8 (Optional Extensions) in your research plan, specifically these three items:
Extension 1: Vision Domain (Phase 8.1) Fine-tune ViT-Large on CIFAR-100 or ImageNet with LoRA, and show that LER detects productive phases in vision tasks too. Right now, all your experiments are NLP-only (GLUE + generative text tasks). If LERNA also works for vision, your claim transforms from "an NLP efficiency tool" to "a universal principle about training dynamics." NeurIPS reviewers value generality.
Extension 2: LERNA + Hi-ZFO Combined (Phase 8.2) Show that combining LERNA (temporal: when to compute gradients) with Hi-ZFO (spatial: which parameters to compute gradients for) yields greater savings than either alone. This opens a new research direction called "spatiotemporal compute optimization." NeurIPS loves papers that open new directions.
Extension 3: Open-Source Release (Phase 8.3) Package LERNA as a pip-installable library with < 10 lines to integrate into any HuggingFace training loop. NeurIPS increasingly values reproducibility and practical impact.
